Pourya Naderi

Bio

I am a postdoctoral research fellow supervised by Winston Hide at the Non-coding RNA Laboratory. My research focuses on network and pathway models for analysis of genomic data in complex diseases. Currently, I am working on models for understanding the role of non-coding RNAs in resilience to Alzheimers disease (AD) and finding potent therapeutic interventions that can alter disease mechanisms in AD.

Education and training

Beth Israel Deaconess Medical Center, Harvard Medical School | Boston, MA

Postdoctoral Research Fellow | 2019 - Now

University of North Carolina at Charlotte | Charlotte, NC

Ph.D.in Computer Science | 2019

Sharif University | Tehran, Iran

B.S. in Computer Science | 2013
